40|$|Relativistic charged {{particles}} and <b>electromagnetic</b> <b>waves</b> in heterogeneous plasma are {{considered in the}} paper aiming at the theoretical investigation {{of the dynamics of}} capture, confinement in potential pits. The investigation of the strong acceleration of resonance particles <b>by</b> <b>electromagnetic</b> <b>waves</b> of a finite amploitude in heterogeneous plasma is also the aim of the paper. During the investigation the method of large-scale decompositions and the methods of the numerical integration of non-linear equations with variable coefficients have been used. As a result conditions of the capture, longitudinal confinement and acceleration of {{charged particles}} <b>by</b> <b>electromagnetic</b> <b>waves</b> in heterogeneous plasma have been investigated for the first time. The paper results may find their field of application in astrophysics, wave processes in ionisphere and magnetosphere, physics of plasmaAvailable from VNTIC / VNTIC - Scientific & Technical Information Centre of RussiaSIGLERURussian Federatio...|$|R
